Class DuplicateReadDetector

  • java.lang.Object
    • DuplicateReadDetector

  • public final class DuplicateReadDetector
extends java.lang.Object
    Since:
    2-3-2015
    Version:
    1
    Author:
    Sean Spurlin DuplicateReaderDetector is a static class which is used to detect duplicate reads of an RFID tag. It does this by maintaining a list of previously seen RFID tags. DuplicateReadDetector will compare a newly read tag to the existing tags within the collection of read tags and compare the time of the newly read tag to the time that the tag was last read. If the difference in read time is above a certain threshold, then the tag is added to the list of tags. Otherwise the tag is ignored. This list of tags is uploaded to the base periodically and then emptied.

      • findDuplicateTagWithLatestReadTime

        public static TagWrapper findDuplicateTagWithLatestReadTime(TagWrapper recentlyReadTag)
        Finds a tag in the Collection of read tags which shares the same EPC number as the input TagWrapper and has the most recent read time of any other matches in the Collection. In short it returns the entry for the previous time the input tag was read. If the input tag has never been read before then it returns null.
        Parameters:
        recentlyReadTag - - RFID tag which was just read by the RFID reader
        Returns:
        The entry for the previous time the input tag was read or null if there was no matching tag in the collection

      • isDuplicateRead

        public static boolean isDuplicateRead(TagWrapper latestRead)
        Determines if the input tag is a duplicate read by searching through the collection of read tags and finding the time the tag was previously read. If the difference in time between the two reads is within a certain margin, then the tag is deemed to be a duplicate read.
        Parameters:
        latestRead - - The most recent read of an RFID tag
        Returns:
        True if the latestRead is a duplicate; false otherwise
